wiki.summary: "Higher Love" was released as a single by Norwegian record producer Kygo and late American vocalist Whitney Houston. The song was released to streaming and digital download formats on 28 June 2019, by label RCA Records. The song marks Houston's first posthumous release in three years, following the song "Memories" which was released as a duet with Malaysian singer Siti Nurhaliza in December 2016. Houston's cover of the Winwood track originally featured on the Japanese edition of her third studio album, I'm Your Baby Tonight (1990). Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Higher Love" was released as a single by Norwegian record producer Kygo and late American vocalist Whitney Houston. The song was released to streaming and digital download formats on 28 June 2019, by label RCA Records. The song marks Houston's first posthumous release in three years, following the song "Memories" which was released as a duet with Malaysian singer Siti Nurhaliza in December 2016. Houston's cover of the Winwood track originally featured on the Japanese edition of her third studio album, I'm Your Baby Tonight (1990). This version of the track was produced by American musician Narada Michael Walden, and therefore Walden is credited as a producer of "Higher Love" alongside Kygo. Read more on Last.fm.
